      "message": "[🟡 Suggestions] Line 321: Triggering `hardwareService.connectivityChanged(...)` directly from `onActivityStarted` runs the connectivity refresh on the main thread during foreground restoration. If this path touches daemon/network state synchronously, app startup/resume can be delayed or ANR-prone. Dispatch the refresh on an existing background executor/scheduler and keep the lifecycle callback lightweight.\n```suggestion\nscheduledExecutor.execute {\n    hardwareService.connectivityChanged(mPreferencesService.hasNetworkConnected())\n}\n```",
