      "message": "[🟡 Suggestions] Line 329: `startedActivities--` is not guarded. Lifecycle callbacks are expected to be balanced, but defensive clamping avoids a negative foreground count if callbacks arrive unexpectedly during activity recreation or framework edge cases; a negative count would prevent future background detection from working correctly. Consider decrementing only when positive and logging an inconsistent state if it is not.\n```suggestion\nif (startedActivities \u003e 0) {\n    startedActivities--\n} else {\n    Log.w(TAG, \"Activity stopped while no activities were marked as started\")\n}\nif (startedActivities \u003d\u003d 0) {\n    backgroundTimestamp \u003d android.os.SystemClock.elapsedRealtime()\n}\n```",
